{%- comment -%}
  Inline delivery-cost notice rendered under the product price.

  Why: 97% of abandoned checkouts are under the $80 free-ship threshold and 62%
  had a trial code applied. The leak is shipping shock at checkout, not a UX
  bug. Surfacing delivery cost AND the free self-collect option on the PDP
  removes the surprise and lets the customer self-select before they get to
  payment.

  Renders on every product page (Dawn main-product section, after price block).
  No setting flags - simple inline note, brand colour bg.
{%- endcomment -%}

<div class="tbp-pdp-delivery-notice" aria-label="Delivery options">
  <p class="tbp-pdp-delivery-notice-line">
    <span aria-hidden="true">🚚</span>
    <span><strong>Cold-chain delivery from $9</strong> · FREE on orders $100+</span>
  </p>
  <p class="tbp-pdp-delivery-notice-line">
    <span aria-hidden="true">🏪</span>
    <span>Or <strong>self-collect $3</strong> at 5 Siglap Road · more locations coming soon</span>
  </p>
</div>

<style>
  .tbp-pdp-delivery-notice {
    background: var(--tbp-tan-light, #F5EFE0);
    border: 1px solid var(--tbp-tan-mid, #e6dfce);
    border-radius: var(--tbp-radius-md, 12px);
    padding: 10px 14px;
    margin: 12px 0 16px;
    font-family: var(--tbp-font-body, system-ui, sans-serif);
    color: var(--tbp-text-dark, #16433D);
  }
  .tbp-pdp-delivery-notice-line {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 3px 0;
    font-size: 13.5px;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
  .tbp-pdp-delivery-notice-line strong {
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--tbp-primary, #16433D);
  }
  .tbp-pdp-delivery-notice-line span[aria-hidden="true"] {
    font-size: 15px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 18px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .tbp-pdp-delivery-notice {
      padding: 9px 12px;
    }
    .tbp-pdp-delivery-notice-line {
      font-size: 12.5px;
    }
  }
</style>
